      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Serialising Plans for Context Windows"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Plans are often embedded in follow-up LLM prompts (for re-planning, evaluation, or execution). Full JSON is verbose. A compact single-line-per-step format reduces token usage significantly while remaining human-readable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom dataclasses import asdict\n\ndef serialise_flat(steps: list[FlatStep]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Serialise a flat plan to a compact token-efficient string.\n\n    Each line is: <index>. [<tool>] <rationale> | args: <key>=<val>...\n    Keeps the plan readable in the context window without full JSON overhead.\n    \"\"\"\n    lines = []\n    for s in steps:\n        args_str = \" \".join(f\"{k}={repr(v)[:40]}\" for k, v in s.args.items())\n        lines.append(f\"{s.index}. [{s.tool}] {s.rationale} | {args_str}\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\ndef deserialise_to_flat(plan_json: str) -> list[FlatStep]:\n    \"\"\"Parse LLM-produced JSON into FlatStep objects with validation.\"\"\"\n    data = json.loads(plan_json)\n    steps = []\n    for raw in data.get(\"steps\", []):\n        if not all(k in raw for k in (\"index\", \"tool\", \"args\")):\n            raise ValueError(f\"Step missing required fields: {raw}\")\n        steps.append(FlatStep(\n            index=int(raw[\"index\"]),\n            tool=raw[\"tool\"],\n            args=raw[\"args\"],\n            rationale=raw.get(\"rationale\", \"\"),\n        ))\n    return sorted(steps, key=lambda s: s.index)\n\n# Context-efficient representation for long plans:\n# Instead of embedding full JSON in the LLM prompt, use the compact format.\n# Full JSON: ~4 tokens per character  ->  ~300 tokens for a 5-step plan\n# Compact:   ~1.5 tokens per character ->  ~120 tokens for the same plan"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Token budget rule:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " a 5-step flat plan in compact format costs ~120 tokens; the same plan in full JSON costs ~300 tokens. For a 10-step plan embedded in a re-planner prompt, this difference can prevent context overflow."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Validating Plan Structure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before executing any plan, validate its structure programmatically. Structural errors (unknown tool names, gaps in step indices, dangling DAG dependencies) should be caught before the first tool call rather than at runtime:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def validate_flat_plan(\n    steps: list[FlatStep],\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Return a list of validation errors, or empty list if valid.\"\"\"\n    errors = []\n    indices = [s.index for s in steps]\n\n    # Check for duplicate indices\n    if len(indices) != len(set(indices)):\n        errors.append(\"Duplicate step indices found\")\n\n    # Check indices are contiguous starting at 1\n    if sorted(indices) != list(range(1, len(steps) + 1)):\n        errors.append(f\"Indices are not contiguous: {sorted(indices)}\")\n\n    # Check all tools exist\n    for s in steps:\n        if s.tool not in available_tools:\n            errors.append(f\"Step {s.index}: unknown tool '{s.tool}'\")\n\n    # Check required args are present (basic check)\n    for s in steps:\n        if not s.args:\n            errors.append(f\"Step {s.index}: empty args for tool '{s.tool}'\")\n\n    return errors\n\ndef validate_dag_plan(\n    nodes: list[DAGNode],\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> list[str]:\n    errors = []\n    node_ids = {n.id for n in nodes}\n    for n in nodes:\n        if n.tool not in available_tools:\n            errors.append(f\"Node {n.id}: unknown tool '{n.tool}'\")\n        for dep in n.depends_on:\n            if dep not in node_ids:\n                errors.append(f\"Node {n.id}: unknown dependency '{dep}'\")\n    return errors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Converting Between Representations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sometimes you generate a flat plan but later need DAG parallelism, or vice versa. Converters let you start with the simplest representation and upgrade it without regenerating from the LLM:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def flat_to_dag(\n    steps: list[FlatStep],\n    dependency_map: dict[int, list[int]] | None = None,\n) -> list[DAGNode]:\n    \"\"\"Convert a flat plan to a DAG, with optional explicit dependencies.\n\n    If dependency_map is None, assumes each step depends only on the\n    immediately preceding step (strictly sequential DAG).\n    If provided, dependency_map maps step index to list of dependency indices.\n    \"\"\"\n    nodes = []\n    for s in steps:\n        if dependency_map is None:\n            deps = [f\"T{s.index - 1}\"] if s.index > 1 else []\n        else:\n            deps = [f\"T{d}\" for d in dependency_map.get(s.index, [])]\n        nodes.append(DAGNode(\n            id=f\"T{s.index}\",\n            tool=s.tool,\n            args=s.args,\n            depends_on=deps,\n        ))\n    return nodes\n\ndef dag_to_flat(nodes: list[DAGNode]) -> list[FlatStep]:\n    \"\"\"Linearise a DAG into a flat step list via topological sort.\n\n    Loses parallelism information but produces an executable flat plan.\n    Useful when switching from a DAG executor to a simpler flat executor.\n    \"\"\"\n    in_deg = {n.id: len(n.depends_on) for n in nodes}\n    graph  = {n.id: [] for n in nodes}\n    index  = {n.id: n for n in nodes}\n    for n in nodes:\n        for dep in n.depends_on:\n            graph[dep].append(n.id)\n\n    order, done = [], set()\n    while len(done) < len(nodes):\n        ready = [nid for nid, deg in in_deg.items() if deg == 0 and nid not in done]\n        order.extend(ready)\n        done.update(ready)\n        for nid in ready:\n            for s in graph[nid]:\n                in_deg[s] -= 1\n\n    return [\n        FlatStep(index=i + 1, tool=index[nid].tool,\n                 args=index[nid].args, rationale=\"\")\n        for i, nid in enumerate(order)\n    ]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Practical pattern:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " generate a flat plan (cheapest LLM call), then ask the LLM to annotate dependencies in a second call: 'Given this flat plan, which steps can run in parallel? Return a dependency_map.' Then convert using "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "flat_to_dag()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
